title.narrative: Girls and boys under age five, school-age children, young girls and women have increased and more equitable access to qualitypreventative nutrition services.

description.narrative: UNICEF’s support to the Government of South Sudan to deliver quality promotional and preventative nutrition services to women, girls and boys, resulted in supplementing 93 per cent of children aged 6 to 59 months with vitamin A and treating 86 per cent of children aged 1 to 5 years against worm infestation, in 77 out of 79 counties. In addition, knowledge on adequate IYCF practices in over 2.1;million caregivers / mothers of children under two years old was supported by enhancing the capacity of 3,761;health and nutrition workers on counselling and promotion of good caring and feeding practices.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:28/12/2021
